{
  "texts": [
    "Let P i denote the ith-row of P. We first prove that P must have at least one nonzero below-diagonal entry.",
    "That is, we claim that there exists i such that P i = e j for j < i.",
    "To see this, let i be the index of the last row which is not equal to its corresponding elementary basis vector e i.",
    "(By the fact that P is not the identity, there must some such row index.)",
    "Since for all j > i, the jth row is equal to e j, the last d -i entries of P i must be zero."
  ]
}